The paper is about preference queries in relational databases, which is a topic closely related to database systems (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the use of preference relations and the elicitation of relative attribute importance, which are topics commonly studied in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also involves the study of properties and computational complexity, which are topics in data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG).
